You are given a single number n, and your task is to print a square pattern using the * symbol.
The pattern should have n rows and n columns — forming a perfect square.
This problem strengthens your understanding of nested loops and equal-dimensioned 2D printing.
Input Format

A single integer n representing both rows and columns.
Constraints

1≤n≤100
Output Format

Print a square of n × n made of * symbols
Each row should be on a new line, with no trailing spaces
Sample Input 0

4
Sample Output 0

****
****
****
****
Sample Input 1

2
Sample Output 1

**
**

import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class Solution {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
       
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        int n=sc.nextInt();
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<n;j++){
                System.out.print("*");
            }
            System.out.println();
        }
        sc.close();
    }
}
